%I A395490 #14 Apr 29 2026 02:52:00
%S A395490 1,1,1,1,5,1,1,19,19,1,1,65,193,65,1,1,216,1511,1511,216,1,1,719,
%T A395490 10443,23293,10443,719,1,1,2423,67733,290291,290291,67733,2423,1,1,
%U A395490 8285,425065,3198397,6022529,3198397,425065,8285,1
%N A395490 Triangle read by rows: coefficients of reciprocal polynomials refining A367255.
%C A395490 Define an integer-valued polynomial p_n(x) = Product_{i=2..n-1} ((n + 1)*x + i) * ((3*n + 1)*(x + x^2) + n) / n!. Then the n-th row describes the numerator of the generating function Sum_{k >= 0} p_n(k) t^k as a rational function.
%C A395490 The cases when n = 0, 1 are a bit special, involving some cancellations.
%F A395490 Numerator of the generating function of values of p_n(x) = Product_{i=2..n-1} ((n + 1) * x + i) * ((3*n + 1) * (x + x^2) + n) / n!.
%e A395490 The first few rows are:
%e A395490   1;
%e A395490   1, 1;
%e A395490   1, 5, 1;
%e A395490   1, 19, 19, 1;
%e A395490   1, 65, 193, 65, 1;
%e A395490   1, 216, 1511, 1511, 216, 1;
%o A395490 (SageMath)
%o A395490 x = polygen(QQ, 'x')
%o A395490 t = x.parent()[['t']].gen()
%o A395490 def row(n):
%o A395490     if n < 2: return [1] * (n + 1)
%o A395490     pn = prod((n+1)*x+i for i in range(2, n)) * ((3*n+1)*(x+x**2)+n) / factorial(n)
%o A395490     poly = (1 - t)**(n + 1) * sum(pn(k) * t**k for k in range(n + 1)).O(n + 1)
%o A395490     return poly.coefficients()
%Y A395490 Row sums are A367255.
%Y A395490 Similar to A108267, A395571, A394704.
%K A395490 nonn,tabl,new
%O A395490 0,5
%A A395490 _F. Chapoton_, Apr 25 2026
